### Key positioning decisions

- No photo on any resume
- No "non-traditional background" framing (per Trini: "there is no traditional consulting background")
- AccessBuddy: "live with real users" not "commercial" or "paying" (first tenant not yet paying)
- $100M figure used for SLSA federation where referenced
- LIMSOC framed as national scaling strategy (the work was real), but not claimed as a national product
- McKinsey letter uses generalist framing (analytical depth, broader problems, any industry) not digital/tech-specific
- EY letter honestly addresses M&A gap and reframes around transferable skills
- Comparison to other candidates removed from all letters per Nick's feedback
- All letters red-teamed for filler, generic openers, list-like structure, and abrupt endings

