Key decisions tranche 2:
- Heidi: Extensive Q1 answer covering parents in healthcare, data-as-product experience at Macquarie, SLSA/LSV data work, both-sides-of-the-table differentiator, data diagnosis depth, defence production discipline. Q2 answer: Sue (Macquarie domain architect, problem-first thinking) and Kirsty (LSV COO, stepping into unfamiliar domains with structure and curiosity). "Strong opinions loosely held" called out as personal resonance with Heidi's culture.
